cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.DS, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the design and evaluation of a system that combines human and machine computation elements for processing data streams. It involves the use of crowdsourcing tasks and human intelligence in stream processing, which falls under the category of human-centered computing (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the design principles and evaluation metrics for the system, which can be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper presents a case study that applies the proposed framework to a real system, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
